            <listitem><para>interface <link linkend="_interface_luthetus_1_1_text_editor_1_1_razor_lib_1_1_text_editors_1_1_models_1_1_i_text_editor_edit_context">Luthetus.TextEditor.RazorLib.TextEditors.Models.ITextEditorEditContext</link></para>

<para>If one invokes, &quot;_ = editContext.GetViewModelModifier(viewModelKey);&quot;.<?linebreak?> Then a side effect occurs where the view model with the provided viewModelKey, will be marked as a having been modified.<?linebreak?> After a Post is finished, the text editor service iterates over all &apos;modified&apos; view models and re-renders them.<?linebreak?> This behavior is a bit hacky since it requires some amount of &apos;hidden knowledge&apos;.<?linebreak?> To get a view model without marking it as modified, use the optional parameter, &apos;isReadonly&apos; and set it to &apos;true&apos;.<?linebreak?> The main reason for making this comment, is that I sometimes assign the result of &apos;GetViewModelModifier&apos; to discard.<?linebreak?> When I do this it feels especially hacky, so I want to leave a paper trail of what I mean by that statement.<?linebreak?>. </para>
